This memorandum, dated July 8, 2009, is from President Barack Obama to the Secretary of State regarding the Palestinian Authority. The President is invoking his authority as President of the United States to waive the restrictions on providing funds to the Palestinian Authority. He certifies that it is important to the national security interests of the United States to waive these provisions and provide funds appropriated to carry out chapter 4 of part II of the Foreign Assistance Act to the Palestinian Authority. The Secretary of State is directed to transmit this determination to Congress, along with a report, and to publish the determination in the Federal Register.